README.md
     5‚Üí# Tomli
     6‚Üí
     7‚Üí> A lil' TOML parser
     8‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    32‚Üí## Intro<a name="intro"></a>
    33‚Üí
    34‚ÜíTomli is a Python library for parsing [TOML](https://toml.io).
    35‚ÜíVersion 2.4.0 and later are compatible with [TOML v1.1.0](https://toml.io/en/v1.1.0).
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    50‚Üí## Installation<a name="installation"></a>
    51‚Üí
    52‚Üí```bash
    53‚Üípip install tomli
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    56‚Üí## Usage<a name="usage"></a>
    57‚Üí
    58‚Üí### Parse a TOML string<a name="parse-a-toml-string"></a>
    59‚Üí
    60‚Üí```python
    61‚Üíimport tomli
    62‚Üí
    63‚Üítoml_str = """
    64‚Üí[[players]]
    65‚Üíname = "Lehtinen"
    66‚Üínumber = 26
    67‚Üí
    68‚Üí[[players]]
    69‚Üíname = "Numminen"
    70‚Üínumber = 27
    71‚Üí"""
    72‚Üí
    73‚Üítoml_dict = tomli.loads(toml_str)
    74‚Üíassert toml_dict == {
    75‚Üí    "players": [{"name": "Lehtinen", "number": 26}, {"name": "Numminen", "number": 27}]
    76‚Üí}
    77‚Üí```
